      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello! I am an undergraduate student currently studying physics at Grinnell College in Grinnell, IA.
There I work as mentor at the 
&lt;a href=&#34;http://dasil.sites.grinnell.edu&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Data Analysis and Social Inquiry Lab&lt;/a&gt; and participate in research into dwarf galaxy evolution with the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.grinnell.edu/academics/majors-concentrations/physics-astronomy&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Physics Department&lt;/a&gt; in collaboration with the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://nbody.shop/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;N-Body Shop&lt;/a&gt;.
I also work with the University of Florida 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.astro.ufl.edu/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Astronomy Department&lt;/a&gt; and the 
&lt;a href=&#34;http://simba.roe.ac.uk/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;SIMBA simulation team&lt;/a&gt; to study massive quiescent galaxies.
I am also an avid photographer and enjoy exploring art, design, architecture, and urban planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This personal website is intended to showcase both astrophysics research projects and other artistic/academic endeavors.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
